To observe all of the possible neutrino oscillation phenomena one would ideally ask for pure neutrino beams of different flavors, and a detector which could identify the three possible leptons in the final state of a charged current interaction. Traditional neutrino beams contain predominantly νμsubscript𝜈𝜇italic-nu POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-mu POSTSUBSCRIPT:end
